           = (z * |/y) * y   by group_assc
     hence x = z * |/y       by group_rcancel
   Only-if part: x = z * |/y ==> x * y = z
     x * y = (z * |/y) * y   by substituting x
           = z * ( |/y * y)   by group_assoc
           = z * #e          by group_linv
           = z               by group_rid
*)
(* still, the first proof is easier. *)

(* Theorem: [Solve right unknown] x * y = z <=> y = |/x * z *)
(* Proof:
   If part: x * y = z ==> y = |/x * z
